How do you keep track like the capital invested the returns in the profits on all these new growth initiatives? Because like you said nothing seems like fluff at all, it all seems very real. It's not just any PowerPoint stuff you guys are throwing up. How do you keep track of that? And then maybe sort of the follow on to that when you think about Dubai and 4,000 Cruise origins floating around, you know I don't know if you can even sketch the economics for us or what that means. I mean, I would guess that's a few hundred million dollars of EBIT, you know, that would be sticky and not volatile like the rest of, you know, we're not a lot more or less volatile than the rest of the company.

